land, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Carnwath, South Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Carnwath, Lanarkshire, Schotland","Scotland":"Schotland"},"en":{"1325–1345":"1325–1345","1329–1380":"1329–1380","1345–1400":"1345–1400","1345–1403":"1345–1403","1300–Male":"1300–Deceased","1403":"1403","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","about 1345":"about 1345","1380":"1380","1329":"1329","Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland":"Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland","Picardie, France":"Picardie, France","Carnwarth, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Carnwath, South Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Carnwath, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Preston","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","habitational name from one of the many places (most notably one in Lancashire) so called from Old English <i>prēost</i> ‘priest’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘farmstead, estate’.","occasionally from Middle English <i>prest</i> + <i>son</i> ‘son of the priest’. Priests were forbidden marriage but many produced illegitimate offspring."],"variants":[{"name":"Presson","meanings":["English (Cheshire and Lancashire): variant of   Preston  .","French: occupational name for a presser of wine or oil, from a derivative of <i>presser</i> ‘to press’."]},{"name":"Prestwich","meanings":["English (Lancashire): habitational name from a place in Lancashire (now Greater Manchester), so called from Old English <i>prēost</i> ‘priest’ + <i>wīc</i> ‘outlying settlement’, or from other places with the same derivation. Variants such as <i>Prestidge</i>, <i>Prestage</i>, etc., parallel the local pronunciation of the Lancashire name. Compare   Preston  ."]}]},{"name":"Janet","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a diminutive of   Jane  , already in common use in the Middle English period. It remained in use in Scotland and in some parts of England well into the 17th century and was revived at the end of the 19th century to much more widespread use, while still retaining its popularity in Scotland. Since the 1960s, however, it has rather gone out of fashion in Britain."],"variants":[{"name":"Jannet","meanings":["Originally a diminutive of   Jane  , already in common use in the Middle English period. It remained in use in Scotland and in some parts of England well into the 17th century and was revived at the end of the 19th century to much more widespread use, while still retaining its popularity in Scotland. Since the 1960s, however, it has rather gone out of fashion in Britain."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Janet Preston was born in 1325, in Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland as the daughter of Sir Thomas Preston of Craigmiller. She married Walter de Somerville about 1345, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1345, in Picardie, France, at the age of 20."},"et":{"1325–1345":"1325–1345","1329–1380":"1329–1380","1345–1400":"1345–1400","1345–1403":"1345–1403","1300–Male":"1300–Surnud","1403":"1403","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","about 1345":"umbes 1345","1380":"1380","1329":"1329","Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland":"Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland","Picardie, France":"Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Carnwarth, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Carnwath, South Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Carnwath, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"fi":{"1325–1345":"1325–1345","1329–1380":"1329–1380","1345–1400":"1345–1400","1345–1403":"1345–1403","1300–Male":"1300–Kuollut","1403":"1403","1325":"1325","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","1300":"1300","about 1345":"noin 1345","1380":"1380","1329":"1329","Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland":"Craigmillar, Midlothian, Scotland","Picardie, France":"Picardie, Ranska","Carnwarth, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Carnwath, South Lanarkshire, Scotla